On 2/8/2019 at 11:13 AM, The_Arcitect said:

7/8 good idea, now who is this reckless?

I used to date a girl who was at another college, and I used to have to drive a ways to get there.  Passing through this one small town, I see a sign that says, "Caution: Low flying Aircraft".   Then I see I'm coming up to a side street to my right.   I then realize it's not a street, but the runway pavement joins up to the road!  I then see the runway has  stop sign at the end of it.   Which had me utterly confused till a few trips later, I saw someone drive down it in a car.   For the first 20 feet or so, the runway doubles as the driveway for the airport.    So yeah, this sign would be very applicable here.

And in this case, the airport consisted of a paved, but not very flat runway, a couple sheds that were used as hangers, and a windsock, so not a high traffic airport.
